Program: The Forum
Title: 04/06/2011 GMT
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00gyhh2
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 5 Jun 2011
It’s an issue high on the political agenda in many countries, but do we really understand how migration affects the countries the migrants leave behind? Is it brain drain or brain gain? And if globalisation is changing the world’s people, what about its plants and its music? This week’s focus is on movement across our shrinking world with economist Ian Goldin, world musician Susheela Raman, nature writer Richard Mabey and guest presenter Matthew Taylor. Illustration by Emily Kasriel: migrating sound, society and seeds. Show less